gn=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ucronikrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CronikRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/01 7:56:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3798.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Evil vs. Newt: Evil's Biggest Advantage</span><hr size=1>   There's one main reason that evil has been winning those big scale skurmishes in the middle of a zone like that.  It's not levels, or epics, or any of those other pissant excuses.  It's simply this:  <br>
 <br>
You don't know how to work together as a team.  You're a bunch of fuckin' chiefs, and none of you know how to act like indians.  Without a lot of planning, you can't do a successful major pvp battle, because it's not reflex for you guys to work together.  YOU DON'T KNOW HOW.  You can pvp just fine one on one, and most of the major newt names out there have experience in that category, but very few of you know how to work together as a team, and react quick enough.  You don't know your roles, or what you're supposed to do if so-and-so happens.  You can react fast enough to pumice a splurt, because you've learned that, but what about those big battles? Those epic battles the &quot;bluebies&quot; do day in and day out?  Damn... I'd love to see the shouting that's going on in your guildchats during those battles.  Maybe if you shouted shit in capslock less and used guildchat for more useful information, you'd get something accomplished.<br>
<br>
I thought the same thing a lot of newts did when the server came up.  The bluebie bitches would get owned by the more experienced pvper's.  Well, I've come to a new understanding.  The &quot;bluebie bitches&quot; are learning how to pvp.  They're getting better at it.  What about you guys? Are you getting any better at working together as a unit, and reacting to a big-war situation, or is it just a bunch of individuals running around with their own agendas?<br>
<br>
You can still use whatever excuses you want, whether it be loot, levels, or whatever.  The simple fact is that guilds like ruin know how to work together, and have spent their time VERY well since server up.  Newts have done nothing but further their own personal agendas, and you haven't accomplished much of anything as a team.  I don't know what makes newts think that time is going to HELP them, when they don't seem to be using their time HALF as efficiently as evil is.  Do you really think that things are magically gonna change?  That guilds like ruin will stop getting ubar loots long enough for you to come even CLOSE?  <br>
<br>
Excuses... all excuses.  Any way you cut it, you have the same, if not better, resources that evil has.  You have better lands, with better xp spots (complete with exploitable quests), and better loots.  Way to put all that to use.  So keep complaining and pointing the finger at evil.  Obviously, evil's methods are proving a hell of a lot more effective in pvp than yours are. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uharpeyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harpeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/01 8:01:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3798.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evil vs. Newt: Evil's Biggest Advantage</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
