<br>
The fact is this: Players begin logging or refuse to go to hostile areas (whether it's pvp or pve) if they die. Groups MUST be run military style in order for them to be successful.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/udarckone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darckone </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/01 8:14:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3798.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evil vs. Newt: Evil's Biggest Advantage</span><hr size=1> Just because someone came from a &quot;Blue&quot; server doesn't mean they don't know how to PvP.  Alot of PvP takes place on a &quot;Blue&quot; server by the way of duels or Arena fights.  Especially on the Evil races of the &quot;Blue&quot; server waiting for boats.  Alot of people duel.  Yes I came from a blue server, but I also dueled very often, and so did alot of other peeps that came from &quot;Blue&quot; servers and have stayed on this server.  This group PvP is alot different thatn 1 on 1 that the &quot;Zekers&quot; are used to.<br>
